---
// Coverage section — "Where we work."
// Quiet editorial pause between Standards and SignOffCTA. No category grid.
---

<section
  id="coverage"
  class="py-32 md:py-44 px-6 md:px-10 lg:px-16"
  style="background: var(--color-bg); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);"
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <h2
      data-reveal
      class="font-serif leading-[1.02] tracking-tight max-w-3xl"
      style="
        color: var(--color-ink);
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 5.2vw, 4.25rem);
      "
    >
      Where we work.
    </h2>

    <div
      data-reveal
      data-reveal-delay="1"
      class="mt-10 md:mt-14 max-w-2xl space-y-5 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed"
      style="color: var(--color-ink-muted);"
    >
      <p>
        We work with small and mid-sized brands that have a defined niche —
        typically in the sub-$50K monthly marketing budget range. The brand
        profile that fits us best is a product company with a real audience, a
        real category, and a brief that hasn't been written yet.
      </p>
      <p>
        If your category is unusual, that's fine. The work is the same.
        Sourcing is sourcing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
